public class Package extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.repeaters.BaseRepeater implements ResourceFolder<Package>
An abstraction for locating and copying Resources in Java packages.

A package object can be constructed with packageForPath(Listener, PackagePath). It implements the ResourceFolder interface because it contains resources, just as Folder does. This means, of course, that methods that accept ResourceFolder can accept either Folders or Packages.

Hierarchy

The parent package can be retrieved with parent() and the path with path(). Sub-packages can be accessed with child(String) or as a resource folder with folder(String).

Resources

Resources in a package can be obtained with ResourceFolder.resources() and ResourceFolder.resources(Matcher). A specific resource can be located with ResourceFolder.resource(String). The resources in a package can be copied to a Folder with ResourceFolder.safeCopyTo(ResourceFolder, WriteMode, ProgressReporter).
